\par The concept of intellectual property - fo
reign to the global Internet culture to start with - became an emblem of Western hegemony and monopolistic practices. Violating copyright, software piracy and hacking became both status symbols and a political declaration of sorts. But the rapid dissemina
tion of programs and information (for instance, illicit copies of reference works) served to level the playing field. 
\par Piracy of material is quite prevalent in the countries in transition. The countries in transition are the second capital of piracy (after 
Asia). Software, films, even books - are copied and distributed quite freely and openly. There are street vendors who deal in the counterfeit products - but most of it is sold through stores and OEMs. 
\par I think that intellectual property will go the way the
